An Act relative to insurance coverage for certain surgeries.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 32A of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
2 section 17W the following section:-
3 Section 17X. The commission shall provide to any active or retired employee of the
4 commonwealth who is insured under the group insurance commission coverage for excess skin
5 removal surgical procedures.
6 SECTION 2. Chapter 118E of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
7 section 10W the following section:-
8 Section 10X. The division shall provide coverage for excess skin removal surgical
9 procedures.
10 SECTION 3. Chapter 175 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
11 section 47ZZ the following section:-
1 of 2

12 Section 47AAA. A policy, contract, agreement, plan or certificate of insurance issued,
13 delivered or renewed within or without the commonwealth shall provide coverage for excess
14 skin removal surgical procedures.
15 SECTION 4. Chapter 176A of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
16 section 8AAA the following section:-
17 Section 8BBB. Any contract between a subscriber and a corporation subject to this
18 chapter, pursuant to an individual or group hospital service plan that is delivered, issued or
19 renewed within the commonwealth shall provide coverage for excess skin removal surgical
20 procedures.
21 SECTION 5. Chapter 176B of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
22 section 4AAA the following section:-
23 4BBB. Any subscription certificate under an individual or group medical service
24 agreement that is delivered, issued or renewed within the commonwealth shall provide coverage
25 for excess skin removal surgical procedures.
26 SECTION 6. Chapter 176G of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
27 section 4SS the following section:-
28 4TT. An individual or group health maintenance contract that is issued, delivered or
29 renewed within the commonwealth shall provide coverage for excess skin removal surgical
30 procedures.
